  "publisher": "SPiER Project (FHIR translation)",
  "description": "FHIR Questionnaire representation of the Patient Health Questionnaire-9 (PHQ-9), a 9-item depression screening instrument. Each item is scored 0-3 (Not at all, Several days, More than half the days, Nearly every day). Total score range: 0-27. Item 9 specifically screens for suicidal ideation and is the primary screening gateway for suicide risk assessment in many clinical workflows. Developed by Drs. Robert L. Spitzer, Janet B.W. Williams, Kurt Kroenke and colleagues.",
  "purpose": "Depression screening with suicide risk identification via Item 9. Severity levels: 0-4 Minimal, 5-9 Mild, 10-14 Moderate, 15-19 Moderately Severe, 20-27 Severe. A positive response on Item 9 (score ≥1) should trigger further suicide risk assessment (e.g., ASQ, C-SSRS).",
  "copyright": "Developed with an educational grant from Pfizer Inc. No permission required to reproduce, translate, display or distribute.",
  "code": [
    {
      "system": "http://loinc.org",
      "code": "44249-1",
      "display": "PHQ-9 quick depression assessment panel"
    }
  ],
